node.description: Recent commercial real estate transactions in New York.
node.content: ["$6.5 MILLION", "215 East Third Street (between Avenue B and Avenue C)", "Manhattan", "Built in 1900, this six-story, 9,660-square-foot building in the East Village has five three-bedroom apartments and a ground-floor commercial space, which is vacant. A four-story carriage house in the rear has four one-bedroom apartments.", "Buyer: The Sabet Group", "Seller: GPS Realty", "Brokers: Aaron Jungreis and Ben Khakshoor of the Rosewood Realty Group", "$14.8 MILLION", "4755 White Plains Road (between East 241st and East 242nd Streets)", "The Bronx", "This 87,900-square-foot, six-story building in Wakefield was built in 1939 and has 83 apartments \u2014 17 two-bedrooms, 49 one-bedrooms and 17 studios \u2014 as well as five retail spaces, which include a grocery store and barbershop, and 11 parking spaces.", "Buyer: 4755WP L.L.C.", "Seller: Ron Rettner", "Brokers: Aaron Jungreis, Ben Khakshoor and Alex Fuchs of the Rosewood Realty Group", "$7 MILLION", "63-14 Queens Boulevard (at 64th Street)", "Queens", "The second floor of this eight-story condominium in Woodside is for sale. The floor is 15,000 square feet and is being used as a student dormitory with 15 short-term-lease apartments. The building was built in 2010 and has a lobby, an outdoor terrace, a recreational space and an underground parking garage with 11 spaces available for the floor.", "Seller: James & Mark 168", "Brokers: Thomas A. Donovan, Eugene Kim, Tommy Lin, Robert Rappa and Bradley Rutkin of B6 Real Estate Advisors."]
